00:05:52.250 --> 00:05:54.944
Storytelling is at the
core of what we do.

00:05:54.944 --> 00:05:57.110
One of the games I'm going
to be talking about today

00:05:57.110 --> 00:05:59.590
is "Episode."

00:05:59.590 --> 00:06:02.040
So storytelling
itself isn't new.

00:06:02.040 --> 00:06:05.140
It's evolved over the course
of thousands of years.

00:06:05.140 --> 00:06:08.370
It's crossed cultures,
generations, continents,

00:06:08.370 --> 00:06:11.402
and it's existed in
many complex forms.

00:06:11.402 --> 00:06:13.360
And when we look at it's
modern-day shape, what

00:06:13.360 --> 00:06:17.400
we're looking at right now is
storytelling in mobile games.

00:06:17.400 --> 00:06:19.650
Episode is the world's
largest network

00:06:19.650 --> 00:06:21.930
for stories created on mobile.

00:06:21.930 --> 00:06:25.260
Right now, we have 73,000
stories with four billion

00:06:25.260 --> 00:06:26.880
episodes viewed.

00:06:26.880 --> 00:06:30.480
We started back in 2014 as
a format for story building

00:06:30.480 --> 00:06:33.750
that was built from the
ground up for mobile.

00:06:33.750 --> 00:06:35.916
This format is still
in its very early days,

00:06:35.916 --> 00:06:37.290
which is very
clear when you look

00:06:37.290 --> 00:06:40.410
at other forms of
modern storytelling

00:06:40.410 --> 00:06:44.080
like television and movies.

00:06:44.080 --> 00:06:46.270
Episode is built
for mobile, meaning

00:06:46.270 --> 00:06:47.890
that it has a portrait format.

00:06:47.890 --> 00:06:50.140
It allows for
bite-sized consumption,

00:06:50.140 --> 00:06:51.790
and it's user-driven.

00:06:51.790 --> 00:06:54.940
You can think of it as
Snapchat meets Netflix.

00:06:54.940 --> 00:06:58.540
Like Snapchat, it's an
interactive entertainment

00:06:58.540 --> 00:07:00.010
built for mobile.

00:07:00.010 --> 00:07:04.900
Like Netflix, Episode is home to
a network of Hollywood caliber

00:07:04.900 --> 00:07:06.090
stories.

00:07:06.090 --> 00:07:09.070
We've been inspired by
both novels and comics.

00:07:09.070 --> 00:07:13.290
Our stories are interactive
and also animated,

00:07:13.290 --> 00:07:16.520
but we're not limited
by print technology.

00:07:16.520 --> 00:07:19.420
We've also drawn from
television and movies.

00:07:19.420 --> 00:07:20.920
We have engaging stories--

00:07:20.920 --> 00:07:23.830
sometimes, even spun
by Hollywood writers.

00:07:23.830 --> 00:07:25.990
But users control
their own pace and how

00:07:25.990 --> 00:07:29.290
they engage with the story.

00:07:29.290 --> 00:07:32.410
Episode is loved by a
mobile-only generation, which

00:07:32.410 --> 00:07:34.960
is comprised largely
of Generation Z, which

00:07:34.960 --> 00:07:37.270
is just now coming of age.

00:07:37.270 --> 00:07:41.260
In a survey that we did
of 36,000 people aged 13

00:07:41.260 --> 00:07:45.730
through 25 in the US, we found
that for women 13 through 25,

00:07:45.730 --> 00:07:50.320
14% are using their phones
for more than 12 hours a day,

00:07:50.320 --> 00:07:54.040
11% are somehow checking
their phones in the shower,

00:07:54.040 --> 00:07:58.120
and of those age
13 through 17, 12%

00:07:58.120 --> 00:08:00.970
check their phones
every few seconds.

00:08:00.970 --> 00:08:03.280
So mobile now needs
a native format

00:08:03.280 --> 00:08:07.190
to address how this generation
interacts with real stories.

00:08:07.190 --> 00:08:10.210
This is a group that's grown-up
entirely with smartphones,

00:08:10.210 --> 00:08:12.700
meaning that they have
always actively participated

00:08:12.700 --> 00:08:15.090
in how they receive
their entertainment.

00:08:15.090 --> 00:08:17.410
So whether it's sending
snaps to friends,

00:08:17.410 --> 00:08:21.460
going climbing with VR, or
watching a video on Musically,

00:08:21.460 --> 00:08:23.290
they expect their
entertainment to be

00:08:23.290 --> 00:08:25.065
both interactive and visual.

00:08:27.810 --> 00:08:31.170
We've also been working with
a handful of IP partners.

00:08:31.170 --> 00:08:33.270
As Hollywood has
taken successful books

00:08:33.270 --> 00:08:36.630
and made them into legendary
film franchises, such as Harry

00:08:36.630 --> 00:08:38.970
Potter and Twilight,
Episode is now

00:08:38.970 --> 00:08:42.299
the first to take great
TV and movie franchises

00:08:42.299 --> 00:08:44.790
and bring them
natively to mobile.

00:08:44.790 --> 00:08:47.670
In 2015, we partnered
with Paramount

00:08:47.670 --> 00:08:49.950
to bring "Mean
Girls" to episode.

00:08:49.950 --> 00:08:52.980
In 2016, we worked with our
friends over at Warner Brothers

00:08:52.980 --> 00:08:55.020
to release "Pretty
Little Liars."

00:08:55.020 --> 00:08:57.750
And this year, we're thrilled
to be working with Universal

00:08:57.750 --> 00:09:00.837
to introduce "Pitch Perfect"
on mobile to the world.

00:09:00.837 --> 00:09:02.670
So this will be out in
the next few months--

00:09:02.670 --> 00:09:04.650
keep an eye open for it.

00:09:04.650 --> 00:09:06.090
And with these
franchise launches,

00:09:06.090 --> 00:09:09.600
Episode has begun to establish
itself as an industry model,

00:09:09.600 --> 00:09:11.310
bringing fans the
ability to actually

00:09:11.310 --> 00:09:16.650
be part of stories that
have these cult followings.

00:09:16.650 --> 00:09:18.930
As YouTube's led to
the rise of streamers,

00:09:18.930 --> 00:09:22.410
and Snapchat's given way to a
new kind of social celebrity,

00:09:22.410 --> 00:09:25.950
Episode has also formed
a new class of creators.

00:09:25.950 --> 00:09:27.660
We've shared our
storytelling tools

00:09:27.660 --> 00:09:30.970
and made them available
to all who are in Episode.

00:09:30.970 --> 00:09:33.000
Episode creators
are now building

00:09:33.000 --> 00:09:35.940
their own long-form
narrative stories.

00:09:35.940 --> 00:09:38.130
Right now, we have over
eight million creators

00:09:38.130 --> 00:09:40.750
who are telling their own
stories within the app.

00:09:40.750 --> 00:09:43.200
And there are five million
weekly active users

00:09:43.200 --> 00:09:45.420
who are reading Episode
original stories

00:09:45.420 --> 00:09:48.540
as well as these Hollywood
inspired stories.

00:09:48.540 --> 00:09:50.850
So as we continue
to build Episode,

00:09:50.850 --> 00:09:53.100
we are thinking constantly,
not only of the stories

00:09:53.100 --> 00:09:55.560
that we're bringing to the
world but of this community

00:09:55.560 --> 00:09:57.060
of storytellers.

00:09:57.060 --> 00:09:59.550
And we're thrilled to be part
of this special and unique

00:09:59.550 --> 00:10:01.920
opportunity to help
give storytellers

00:10:01.920 --> 00:10:04.050
both a platform and a voice.

00:10:04.050 --> 00:10:05.620
Thank you.

